Dendrocalamus strictus

   [5238.jpg]
    Authority   (Roxb.) Nees
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names male bamboo, Calcutta bamboo, bambu' macico
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5238

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A bamboo with dense clumps and with culms 10-15 m tall and 2.5-7.5 cm
   in diameter. The bamboo is deciduous, or evergreen under more moist
   conditions.
   KILLING T
   Frost-hardy within its natural habitat.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. Life-cycle about 20-40 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Male bamboo, Bans, Kiribidru,, Kal mungil, Myinwa.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: Bambusa stricta. Male bamboo can grow 7-17 m high.
   This is the commonest, most widespread and most universally used bamboo
   in India. There it is typically found in hilly country at elevations
   between sea level and 1200 m. Bamboos grow between the latitudes 40°N
   and S. Though the big bamboo forests usually occur between 15-25°N and
   S.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 978 979 984 1006-1008 [TEXT, DRA, FER, LIG, KTMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 427 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 14 [TEMP, RAIN, PH]
